HEADWORD: Recurrency
<hw>Re*cur"ren*cy</hw> <pr>(-r<it>e</it>n*s?)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧currence</ets>.]</ety> <def>The
act of recurring, or state of being recurrent; return; resort;
recourse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I shall insensibly go on from a rare to a frequent
<qex>recurrence</qex> to the dangerous preparations.</q> <rj><qau>I.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recurrent</ent>⟦br⟧
